H0.text: Carbohydrates are the term used to describe organic compounds such as sugars and starches.

H1.text: Fats are the term used to describe organic compounds such as sugars and starches.

H2.text: Proteins are organic compounds such as sugars and starches.

H3.text: Vegetables are the term used to describe organic compounds such as sugars and starches.

A4.text: A carbohydrate is a sugar (saccharide) or a sugar derivative.

A5.text: Together with amino acids, fats, and nucleic acids, the carbohydrates are one of the major families of biomolecules.
